--- DESIGN DECISIONS ---
- Single initial migration file `crates/server/migrations/20250320100000_initial_schema.sql` (forward-only; timestamp prefix for SQLx ordering).
- Table `sessions.git_ref` instead of SQL reserved `ref`.
- Identities: `agent_token_ciphertext` / `git_token_ciphertext` as BYTEA (opaque storage; app-layer encryption later).
- api_keys: `key_hash` TEXT UNIQUE (hash algorithm left to future auth task).
- workers: id TEXT PK, labels JSONB, last_seen_at, host.
- jobs: reclaim_count, assigned_at, completed_at, error_message, pull_request_url, task_input JSONB, FK to sessions and workers.
- logs: table name `logs`, UNIQUE(session_id, line_seq), optional job_id FK.
- Seed: `INSERT INTO identities (id) VALUES ('default');` once per fresh DB (sqlx migration versioning prevents re-run).
- Skipped separate persona/inbox placeholder tables (spec allowed “optional… later”).
- `sqlx::migrate!("./migrations")` path relative to server crate (macro resolves at compile time).

